<subSubSection id="C36265517A50FFD6FFCBFE8CFDDAFDAE" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC736DA7A50FFD6FFCBFE8CFDDAFDAE" blockId="19.[96,751,334,516]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
This species, a very close relative of 
<taxonomicName id="4C784D597A50FFD6FD81FE8DFD73FECD" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[554,689,334,359]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Pavo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cristatus">
<emphasis id="B90CEAC87A50FFD6FD81FE8DFD73FECD" box="[554,689,334,359]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">M. cristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was named for the Icarus of Greek mythology, based on the appearance of a &quot;winged figure&quot; on the fan. It can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C784D597A50FFD6FEE9FE6FFE06FE6F" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[322,452,428,453]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Pavo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cristatus">
<emphasis id="B90CEAC87A50FFD6FEE9FE6FFE06FE6F" box="[322,452,428,453]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">M. cristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the division of the red anteromedial tract of the fan in that species, as well as by several details of the courtship display.
</paragraph>
